commit.message:
Update AUTHORS file (add Roman Zippel)
(fix of commit df2d8771f)

Roman Zippel contributed the initial version of m68k support.

Travis CI: Update autoconf to 2.72 for distcheck

Issue #60 (libatomic_ops).

This fixes mmap detection by configure on CheriBSD.

Use portable 'type' command in autogen.sh to test if libtoolize exists
(fix of commit 7d272176c)

* autogen.sh: Use "type" command (to test if libtoolize exists) instead
of non-portable "which" one.

Do not run libtoolize by autogen.sh if libtoolize is missing
(fix of commit c9ebc1683)

* autogen.sh: Do not run libtoolize if it is not available (i.e. which
command cannot find it); update comment.
Update AUTHORS file (add Bruno Haible)

Fix 'libtool library used but LIBTOOL is undefined' autoreconf error

Install libtool.m4 and ltmain.sh in the build tree before running
autoreconf.  This is needed if autoreconf and libtoolize are available
from the different directories of $PATH.

* autogen.sh: Invoke libtoolize; add comment.

Update shared objects version info to be not lower than in v7.8.x

* CMakeLists.txt (LIBATOMIC_OPS_VER_INFO, LIBATOMIC_OPS_GPL_VER_INFO):
Increment current and age (change version info of libatomic_ops.so and
libatomic_ops_gpl.so to 4:0:3).
* src/Makefile.am (LIBATOMIC_OPS_VER_INFO, LIBATOMIC_OPS_GPL_VER_INFO):
Likewise.
Update ChangeLog file
Update ChangeLog file (set v7.8.2 release date)

Update ChangeLog file (v7.8 changes)
(a cherry-pick of commits d482d3f4e, 4c00f978c from 'release-7_8')
Update ChangeLog file (set v7.6.16 release date)

Update ChangeLog file (v7.6 changes)
(a cherry-pick of commit df7b63038 from 'release-7_6')
Update ChangeLog file (set v7.4.20 release date)

Update ChangeLog file (v7.2 - v7.4 changes only)
(a cherry-pick of commit 6098be600 from 'release-7_4')
GH Actions: Turn on cmake build/test in parallel
Travis CI: Turn on cmake parallel build
AppVeyor CI: Turn on cmake parallel build

Fix GH Actions badge name in README
(fix of commit fc422be8d)
GH Actions: Turn on verbose build mode and fail on compiler warnings
GH Actions: Rename config file to match workflow name
GH Actions: Fix builds on Windows by clang and gcc

GH Actions: Remove non-working architectures (other than amd64)

Note: more work is needed to enable testing on other architectures (in
a container).

Fix 'undefined reference to __atomic_load/store/cas_16' Mingw64-gcc error
(fix of commit 759fa976)

Issue #34 (libatomic_ops).

gcc/x64 (as of gcc-12.2, including that of mingw64) requires -latomic
flag in case of double-word atomic operations use.

* src/atomic_ops/sysdeps/gcc/x86.h [!AO_DISABLE_GCC_ATOMICS
&& !__APPLE_CC__ && !__clang__ && !AO_PREFER_BUILTIN_ATOMICS
&& !AO_THREAD_SANITIZER] (AO_SKIPATOMIC_double_compare_and_swap_ANY,
AO_SKIPATOMIC_DOUBLE_LOAD_STORE_ANY): Define only if __x86_64__;
define regardless of __MINGW32__ and gcc version; update comment.
GH Actions: change workflow name to 'cmake build'

Remove total-lines badge from README

The lines-of-code badge is not working stably.
Add GH Actions build status badge to README
GH Actions: initial setup of build and test using CMake
.gitignore: Ignore /build folder

Workaround test_atomic 'saw release store out of order' error on ppc64
(fix of commit 418dfb502)

Issue #58 (libatomic_ops).

* tests/test_atomic.c [(!AO_NO_PTHREADS || !AO_USE_PTHREAD_DEFS)
&& AO_HAVE_store_release_write && AO_HAVE_load_acquire_read
&& __powerpc64__ && !__clang__] (counter1): Do not define as static.

Travis CI: Test -D AO_STACK_USE_CPTR with clang instead of gcc
(fix of commit 1a7d31cb2)
